cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.CR 

This paper is about developing a distribution correction approach for deep neural networks to avoid overfitting imperfect training data. The paper focuses on classification tasks and proposes a method to make supervised learning robust with imperfectly labeled input. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, since the paper deals with classification tasks, it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
